---
title: iOS sign-in round trip
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    box rgb(232, 240, 254) App code
        participant App as App UI / ViewModel
    end
    box rgb(232, 245, 233) oauth-kmp library
        participant PKCEFlow as PKCEFlow (commonMain)
        participant Session as IosWebAuthSession
    end
    box rgb(255, 243, 224) OS
        participant Sheet as ASWebAuthenticationSession
    end
    box rgb(245, 245, 245) Server
        participant Server as OAuth server
    end

    App->>PKCEFlow: startSignIn()
    Note over PKCEFlow: authState = WAITING_FOR_AUTHORIZATION_CODE<br/>generate verifier, build sign-in URL with S256 challenge
    PKCEFlow->>Session: startSignIn(signInUrl, redirectUrl)
    Session->>Sheet: ASWebAuthenticationSession(signInUrl,<br/>callbackURLScheme, completion).start()
    Note over Sheet: ★ control is with the OS —<br/>user signs in inside the system browser sheet
    Sheet->>Server: GET oauth/authorize (user signs in and approves)
    Server-->>Sheet: 302 redirect to exampleapp://oauth?code=…
    Note over Sheet: the session watches for the redirect scheme and captures<br/>the redirect itself — the URL is never routed through<br/>the app's URL-handling machinery
    Sheet-->>Session: completion(callbackURL, error)
    Session-->>PKCEFlow: completionHandler(url, errorMessage)<br/>= continueSignInWithCallbackOrError
    Note over PKCEFlow: extract ?code=…<br/>authState = EXCHANGING_AUTHORIZATION_CODE
    PKCEFlow->>Server: POST oauth/token (code + verifier) on applicationScope/ioDispatcher
    Server-->>PKCEFlow: TokenResponse (access + refresh tokens)
    Note over PKCEFlow: authState = FINISHED(tokenResponse)
    PKCEFlow-->>App: observed via authState StateFlow
